This is an initial incomplete version of ONAP data layer (only includes mariadb)

get_secret.sh will fill variables in input-overrides.yaml and create a new file called data-overrides.yaml 

To deploy data layer: 
helm install --set global.masterPassword=pleaseMakeMeMoreSecure data .

Then to deploy ONAP:
Run the script to create data-overrides.yaml at the needed path (remember to pass external data layer namespace)
./get_secret.sh data-layer-namespace
Then we deploying ONAP, pass the file data-overrides.yaml located at ../kubernetes/onap/resources/environments/data-overrides.yaml to helm deploy

To test nbi with external mariadb, run the following:
helm deploy dev local/onap -f disable-allcharts.yaml -f data-overrides.yaml --set global.masterPassword=notSecureChangeMe --set nbi.enabled=true